Feature: API Interface

    The Browsermob API Interface interacts with the Java server.

    Scenario: As a user I want to get a list of proxies.

    Scenario: As a user I want to create a new HAR.

    Scenario: As a user I want to create a new page on an existing HAR.

    Scenario: As a user I want to shut down the proxy and close the port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to get the HAR content attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to get the current whitelist attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to update the current whitelist attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to remove the current whitelist attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to get the current blacklist attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to update the current blacklist attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to remove the current blacklist attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to update the current proxy limit attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to get the current proxy limit attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to add headers to requests attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to add hosts to requests attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to add proxy authentication (Basic) attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to update the waits on all requests being made attached to a port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to update the proxy timeout on all requests attached to the port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to update the proxy redirection on all requests attached to the port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to remove the proxy redirection on all requests attached to the port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to add retry counts on all requests attached to the port.

    Scenario: As a user I want to remove the proxy dns cache on all requests attached to the port.